    "Our first aim is to prove that the chemical collision frequency ν CH, acting as a multiplicative operator on f ∈ L 2 (R 3, µ µ µ -1/2) and defined componentwise by(34) ν CH i (v) = R 3 ×S 2 H |v -v * | 2 - 2E hk ij m ij B hk ij (|v -v * |, cos θ)µ j (v *)dv * dσ, v ∈ R 3,for any reaction S i + S j → S h + S k, can be bounded above and below by the function ⟨v⟩ γ.",
